<p>Shared coding conventions allow teams to collaborate effectively. This rule checks that all C++ concept names match a provided regular
expression.</p>
<h2>Noncompliant Code Example</h2>
<p>With default provided regular expression <code>^[A-Z][a-zA-Z0-9]*$</code>:</p>
<pre>
template &lt;class T&gt;
concept integral = std::is_integral_v&lt;T&gt;; // Noncompliant
</pre>
<h2>Compliant Solution</h2>
<pre>
template &lt;class T&gt;
concept Integral = std::is_integral_v&lt;T&gt;; // Compliant
</pre>